The following are major news items in leading Japanese
newspapers today. Asahi: -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin arrived in
Honolulu Sunday, beginning a visit to the United States aimed at
deepening understanding between the two countries. Asahi, Yomiuri,
Mainichi, Nihon Keizai: -- Stocks plunged Monday in Tokyo, New York and
London in a chain reaction. Mainichi: -- Seventy percent of Japan's
high school students don't read even one book a month, a survey shows.
Yomiuri: -- A bank funded entirely by the Philippine government in
Japan is involved in "underground banking" transfers of 6 billion yen
(about 50 million U.S. dollars) a year to the Philippines, sources said
Monday.
